# Monorepo lockfile agent gate (umbraculum-dev)

**Audience:** agents only. The operator is an analyst ‚Äî **you** enforce lockfile policy; do not tell them to "avoid X in the future."

## When agents MUST run the gate

Run skill **`monorepo-lockfile-gate`** when **any** of these apply:

| Trigger | Examples |
|---------|----------|
| Root lockfile edit | `package-lock.json` changed (regen, merge, bump, Tamagui/native hoist refresh) |
| Workspace dep bump | Any `package.json` under `apps/`, `services/`, `packages/` that affects root install |
| Forbidden file present | `services/api/package-lock.json` on disk or in `git status` |
| Pre-push with lockfile commit | Commit touches `package-lock.json` |
| CI symptom | GHA `npm ci` / `Invalid: lock file's ‚Ä¶ does not satisfy ‚Ä¶` on lint, typecheck, native-deps |

**Skip** on pure docs-only prose with no manifest/lockfile surface (`apparatus: override` still valid).

## Hard rules (agent-owned ‚Äî not operator homework)

1. **Root `package-lock.json` is the only lockfile for `@umbraculum/api` and all npm workspaces.** CI runs `npm ci` at repo root in **`node:20-slim` / npm 10**.
2. **Never commit `services/api/package-lock.json`.** It is gitignored and forbidden. If it exists: **`rm -f services/api/package-lock.json`** ‚Äî do not `git add` it (including `-f`).
3. **Never regenerate root `package-lock.json` on the host** for commits. Use **`node:20-slim`** (skill commands). Host-only regen causes `@swc/helpers`-class drift and red GHA.
4. **After any root lockfile change, before commit:** run **`npm run check:lockfiles`** (agent runs it ‚Äî not the operator).
5. **Before push** when the commit includes `package-lock.json`: **`npm run verify:pre-push`** on a **clean committed tree** (agent runs it).

## Intentional extra lockfiles (do not delete)

`apps/web/package-lock.json`, `apps/web/e2e/package-lock.json`, `packages/platform/test-mcp/package-lock.json`, `docs-site/vendor/brochure/package-lock.json` ‚Äî see `DEVELOPMENT.md` ¬ß npm lockfiles.

## Agent anti-patterns

| Anti-pattern | Why it fails |
|---|---|
| Commit host-only `npm install` lockfile | GHA `npm ci` rejects sync (`@swc/helpers` drift) |
| `git add services/api/package-lock.json` | Forbidden; pollutes review; not CI SoT |
| Tell operator "regen lockfile before push" | Wrong paradigm ‚Äî **agent** regens and verifies |
| `verify:pre-push` green with empty diff vs `origin/master` only | Path-aware T2 may skip jobs; lockfile commits still need **`check:lockfiles`** in validate |
| Rely on docs-readmes alone when pushing lockfile-only fix | Run **`check:lockfiles`** + **`npm ci`** proof in container |

## Enforcement (umbraculum-dev)

Plugin `alwaysApply` is **not reliably enforced** by Cursor. **umbraculum-dev** commits a verbatim copy at `.cursor/rules/80-monorepo-lockfile-agent-gate.mdc` ‚Äî agents in that repo must treat **that file** as binding.

Mechanical gates: `scripts/check-monorepo-lockfiles.sh`, `scripts/check-root-lockfile-sync.sh`, `npm run check:lockfiles`, **`verify-slice.sh` T2 validate** (always runs lockfile checks), ci-parity **`docs-readmes`** job.

Runbook: skill **`monorepo-lockfile-gate`**. Human SoT: `DEVELOPMENT.md` ¬ß npm lockfiles.
